FAMILY 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC7FFEBA2FB790395270803" authority="GRAY, 1849" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1849" box="[1010,1351,601,626]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Chiroteuthidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">
CHIROTEUTHIDAE 
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFC7FFEBA5CD790395270803" author="Gray JE" box="[1220,1351,601,626]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" refId="ref14816" refString="Gray JE. 1849. Catalogue of the Mollusca in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Cephalopoda Artepedia. London: Trustees of the British Museum." type="book" year="1849">GRAY, 1849</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC7FFEBA2A879D8955C08EA" blockId="14.[929,1340,642,667]" box="[929,1340,642,667]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">(17 SPECIES IN FIVE OR SIX GENERA)</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9AA9651CFFC7FFEBA23279F194B30FDB" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC7FFEBA23279F194220EB8" blockId="14.[827,1443,682,1226]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC7FFEBA23279F193D408B1" box="[827,948,683,704]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC7FFEBA2C879F0941E08B1" authorityName="GRAY" authorityYear="1849" box="[961,1150,682,704]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" rank="superFamily" superFamily="Chiroteuthoidea">Chiroteuthoidea</taxonomicName>
with arm suckers in two series and tentacle suckers in four series or absent; club divided into two or three sections with symmetrical protective membranes; with enlarged ventral arms having expanded lateral membranes modified into sheaths for the tentacles; head with a long neck and usually with a brachial pillar in adults, with an indistinct eyelid sinus, with stalked olfactory organs, without occipital folds; funnel–mantle locking apparatus usually oval and with a series of knobs known as tragus and antitragus; tail with lateral ornamentation, lost in adults of some genera but retained in others; characteristic paralarval 
<typeStatus id="0D088835FFC7FFEBA5637F4194FD0E41" box="[1130,1181,1051,1072]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">type</typeStatus>
known as ‘doratopsis’ with an elongated chambered neck and brachial pillar, and with vesicular tissue in the posterior mantle, with vesiculated arms in advanced paralarvae, and with gladius extending beyond the fins and supporting ornamented structures.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D20C3697FFC7FFEBA2327FA194B30FDB" blockId="14.[827,1443,1274,1450]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC7FFEBA2327FA193D70F61" box="[827,951,1274,1296]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">Remarks:</emphasis>
Adults of the paedomorphic genus 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC7FFEBA2327E43941F0F5F" authority="Pfeffer, 1912" authorityName="Pfeffer" authorityYear="1912" box="[827,1151,1305,1327]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Chiroteuthidae" genus="Planctoteuthis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC7FFEBA2327E4393840F5F" box="[827,996,1305,1326]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">Planctoteuthis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B6224B66FFC7FFEBA2E27E43941F0F5F" author="Pfeffer G" box="[1003,1151,1305,1327]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" pagination="1 - 815" refId="ref16383" refString="Pfeffer G. 1912. Die Cephalopoden der Plankton-Expedition. Zugleich eine monographische ubersicht der Oegopsiden Cephalopoden. Ergebnisse der Plankton-Expedition der Humboldt-stiftung 2: 1 - 815." type="journal article" year="1912">Pfeffer, 1912</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
retain the primary club; hence, the morphological characters related to the tentacle morphology in this diagnosis do not apply to this genus. The funnel–mantle locking apparatus of 
<taxonomicName id="15B34D14FFC7FFEBA2327ECE940D0FD8" baseAuthorityName="Verany" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[827,1133,1428,1449]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Chiroteuthidae" genus="Grimalditeuthis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Oegopsida" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="bonplandi">
<emphasis id="E0C7EA85FFC7FFEBA2327ECE940D0FD8" box="[827,1133,1428,1449]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1226">Grimalditeuthis bonplandi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is fused.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
